# Constant Fold Boolean Expressions

## Description

Simplifies boolean expressions with known constant operands:
- `TRUE AND x` -> `x`
- `FALSE AND x` -> `FALSE`
- `TRUE OR x` -> `TRUE`
- `FALSE OR x` -> `x`
- `NOT TRUE` -> `FALSE`
- `NOT FALSE` -> `TRUE`

**When to apply**: Boolean expression with at least one constant operand.

**Why it works**: Boolean algebra identities eliminate unnecessary
evaluation. Cascading with other constant folding rules can
eliminate entire predicate trees.

## Implementation

```rust
rw!("and-true-left"; "(and true ?x)" => "?x"),
rw!("and-true-right"; "(and ?x true)" => "?x"),
rw!("and-false-left"; "(and false ?x)" => "false"),
rw!("and-false-right"; "(and ?x false)" => "false"),
rw!("or-true-left"; "(or true ?x)" => "true"),
rw!("or-true-right"; "(or ?x true)" => "true"),
rw!("or-false-left"; "(or false ?x)" => "?x"),
rw!("or-false-right"; "(or ?x false)" => "?x"),
rw!("not-true"; "(not true)" => "false"),
rw!("not-false"; "(not false)" => "true"),
rw!("not-not"; "(not (not ?x))" => "?x"),
```

## Test Cases

```sql
-- Before
SELECT * FROM t WHERE TRUE AND active = true;
-- After
SELECT * FROM t WHERE active = true;
```

```sql
-- Before
SELECT * FROM t WHERE FALSE OR status = 'open';
-- After
SELECT * FROM t WHERE status = 'open';
```

